    "summary": "Exploring the use of novel land surface modeling and multi-source satellite data fusion to address the global challenges of food and water security. My work seeks to develop and implement operationally algorithms that improve the spatio-temporal representation of physical variables that link our water-food systems from farms to global scales. Specific elements of my work have included the estimation of vegetation dynamics, soil moisture, irrigation, and evapotranspiration by combining earth-observation data across many regions of the world. \n\n- The synergy between multi-spectral and -resolution remote sensing data (microwave, thermal and optical)\n- Remotely sensed soil moisture, crop water use, and vegetation for agricultural applications\n- Observation-driven monitoring and management strategies for farmers and decision-makers",
